FM Acoustics of Switzerland (also FM Acoustics Ltd.) is a manufacturer of high-end and professional audio components including phono and harmonic linearizers, preamplifiers, power amplifiers, electronic crossovers, microphone amplifiers and (up until the 1980s) loudspeakers. Since [1993], it is based in Horgen, Switzerland on the shore of Lake Zurich.
FM comes from the intended company name "For Music and Acoustics" which could not be used due to Swiss law.
